# 335-port: 3.3.5 TOC file paths MUST use BACKSLASH separators. Upstream (retail) mixes
# them -- Libs\ used backslash but plusmouse's own files used forward slashes (Core/X.lua),
# which retail tolerates but the 3.3.5 client REJECTS ("Error loading" every forward-slash
# file -> the addon loaded zero of its own files). All separators normalized to `\` below.
# 335-port (#5): Core\Compat.lua loads BEFORE Libs\ -- CallbackHandler-1.0 (v8) captures
# `local securecallfunction = securecallfunction` at file scope; Compat must define it first.
Core\Compat.lua

Libs\LibStub\LibStub.lua
Libs\CallbackHandler-1.0\CallbackHandler-1.0.lua
Libs\LibSharedMedia-3.0\lib.xml

